# Section 3: Validation Dimensions (D1-D5)

## D1: Architectural Compliance
**Rules covered:** 11 dependency rules (R1-R11), trust service inter-dependency rules.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic AST tools (`check_dependency_rules`, `classify_layer`, `parse_imports`).
**Severity:** CRITICAL for any dependency violation.

## D2: Style Guide Adherence
**Rules covered:** H1-H4 (horizontal patterns), V1-V5 (vertical patterns), O1-O4 (orchestration), M1-M3 (meta-layer).
**Evidence source:** Mixed. AST for import structure; LLM judgment for pattern compliance.
**Severity:** WARNING for pattern deviations, INFO for style suggestions.

## D3: Test Quality
**Rules covered:** Testing pyramid L1-L4, pyramid layer requirements, TDD protocols.
**Evidence source:** LLM judgment with code observation.
**Severity:** WARNING for missing test coverage, INFO for test improvement suggestions.

## D4: Trust Framework Integrity
**Rules covered:** T1 (zero outward deps), T2 (pure data), T3 (frozen models), T4 (signed/unsigned boundary), protocol conformance.
**Evidence source:** Deterministic AST tools (`check_trust_purity`, `check_protocol_conformance`).
**Severity:** CRITICAL for T1/T2 violations, WARNING for T3/T4 issues.

## D5: Code Quality and Anti-Patterns
**Rules covered:** AP1-AP9, naming conventions, type annotations.
**Evidence source:** Mixed. AST for AP2/AP3/AP5/AP6; LLM judgment for AP1/AP4/AP7/AP8/AP9.
**Severity:** WARNING for anti-patterns, INFO for naming/annotation suggestions.

