# Section 5: Tool Specifications

You have access to the following deterministic tools. Always prefer these over manual inspection for the dimensions they cover.

## parse_imports
```
Input:  {"filepath": "<path to .py file>"}
Output: {"pass": bool, "file": str, "imports": [{"module": str, "names": [str], "line": int, "top_package": str}]}
```
Extracts all imports via AST. No code execution.

## classify_layer
```
Input:  {"filepath": "<path to .py file>"}
Output: {"file": str, "layer": str, "layer_dir": str}
```
Maps file path to grid layer (Trust Foundation, Horizontal Services, Vertical Components, Meta-Layer).

## check_dependency_rules
```
Input:  {"filepath": "<path to .py file>"}
Output: {"pass": bool, "file": str, "layer": str, "violations": [{"rule": str, "file": str, "line": int, "description": str}]}
```
Validates all imports against the 11-rule dependency table. Returns PASS or FAIL with violation details.

## check_trust_purity
```
Input:  {"filepath": "<path to .py file>"}
Output: {"pass": bool, "file": str, "layer": str, "violations": [{"rule": str, "file": str, "line": int, "description": str}]}
```
Checks trust/ files for I/O, logging, storage, or network imports. Only applies to trust/ files.

## check_protocol_conformance
```
Input:  {"adapter_filepath": "<path to adapter .py>", "protocol_name": "<Protocol class name>"}
Output: {"pass": bool, "file": str, "protocol": str, "missing_methods": [str], "violations": [...]}
```
Compares adapter class methods against protocol definition. Reports missing methods.

## detect_anti_patterns
```
Input:  {"filepath": "<path to .py file>"}
Output: {"pass": bool, "file": str, "violations": [{"rule": str, "file": str, "line": int, "description": str}]}
```
Heuristic AST checks for AP2 (vertical-to-vertical imports), AP3 (hardcoded prompts), AP5 (direct I/O in agents), AP6 (BaseModel in utils).

## read_file
```
Input:  {"filepath": "<path to file>"}
Output: File contents as string with line numbers.
```
Read any file for manual inspection when deterministic tools are insufficient.

## search_codebase
```
Input:  {"query": "<search term>", "glob": "<optional file pattern>"}
Output: Matching file paths and line content.
```
Search for patterns across the codebase.

